# Eval case: portfolio-drift-analyzer

IDEA="Build a local read-only portfolio drift analyzer. Ingest holdings CSVs across equity, mutual funds, and fixed deposits, compute current asset allocation, compare against a user-defined target allocation, and a deterministic model quantifies drift per asset class. A local LLM narrates which classes are over/under-weight from structured allocation summaries only. Output a Markdown drift report."

CONTEXT="Target: single investor, laptop-only, no cloud sync. Stack: Python CLI; Pandas; DuckDB (encrypted); Ollama 8B optional. Formats: 3 CSV templates (equity holdings, MF holdings, FD list). Limits: max 5 asset classes; read-only holdings. Non-goals: rebalancing automation; order placement; broker API; live price fetching; cloud LLM default; React UI; multi-user; tax filing. Defer: scheduled price refresh; gold/real-estate classes; what-if rebalancing."
